column5: Only 2 more sleeps to go.  Can't wait to see a whole bunch of familiar and new faces Saturday.
I will be there looking as usual
I will be there looking as usual Take your boat Kalvin with a For Sale sign on it. If you sell, your buying the WINGS and Bruce has the secret sauce
I'll be there hopefully reducing some Muskie gear overstock!
Take your boat Kalvin with a For Sale sign on it. If you sell, your buying the WINGS and Bruce has the secret sauce would do but boats still in the garage
Just sold a rod, so now I have pocket money and hopefully the wife won't notice when I bring home a couple more!
Is this open to the fishing public?
Is this open to the fishing public? Sure is its a tackle swap meet.... and things
Did someone say GTG at Pub fiction?? Oh. yes I did.
Did someone say GTG at Pub fiction?? Oh. yes I did.
See you tomorrow.
Wont be making it this year byes. Sorry for that.
I'll be there!!
I wish I wasn't working today or else I would have gone..
Got a buddy there at the stixnstones booth today go check them out!
Very busy, was there at 8:45 and already a line up to get in. Good Deals, $6.00 X Raps and other Rapalas, $12.00 spools of power pro, stocked up.
It was a great day in Ancaster. Lots of faces. Dave, Calvin, Albert, Jose, Chris, Mike.  Good to see you all. Very crowded for the first 2 hours.

Did well today.  Traded lots of lures.  Some guys are for it and some not. Got a nice bait casting reel for $25.  Wanted to pick up one of those shirts that say "fifty incher" but had to watch my spending.
It was my first trip to the swap. I was very impressed with what was being offered and the prices. I will be back next year with a shopping list. Thanks Spiel for letting me know about it!

Was there from 9.00 till 10.30, met Bruce and bought a few jigs and met Albert and Chris also... spent a few $$$$$$ but final found some... " beno;s and a few eels also"  FINALY... now would like to find a few more
Really enjoyed the swap.  Are there any more in Southern Ontario coming up?
Really enjoyed the swap. Are there any more in Southern Ontario coming up?
Was great seeing you Bruce and Rob. As always a great turn out. It gets bigger every year. Will be at the north GTA swap in a few weeks
